  "course_description": "Traces the gradual incorporation of Africa into an expanding world economy and examines the impact of this incorporation on the development of African societies and modern nation states.",
  "course_notes": "(Same as AFS 221 1) This course traces the history of Africa from the 19th century to the present. We will examine the impact of slavery and colonialism on African societies, economies, and cultures. We will explore the varied responses of African communities to European conquest and domination, the decolonization movements of the 20th century, and some of the challenges faced by independent African nation-states in the last 50 years. This course is introductory and assumes no previous knowledge of African history.",
